<onlyinclude>The '''CZW World Heavyweight Championship''' is the top [[professional wrestling]] [[Championship (professional wrestling)|title]] in the [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Philadelphia]]-based [[Professional wrestling promotion|promotion]] [[Combat Zone Wrestling]]. It was established in [[1999]] at CZW's second show, ''The Staple Gun'', with [[Nick Gage]] winning a [[Battle royal (professional wrestling)|battle royal]].<ref name="staplegun" /> The "world" in the title's name refers to the fact that the title has been defended (and changed hands) several times outside of the [[United States]], including in [[Mexico]],<ref name="czwofficial">{{cite web |url=http://czwrestling.com/titlehistory.html |title=CZW World Heavyweight Championship official title history |accessdate=2007-06-19 |publisher=CZWrestling.com }}</ref> [[England]],<ref name="czwofficial" /> [[Ireland]],<ref name="czwofficial" /> [[Italy]]<ref name="czwofficial" /> and [[Japan]].<ref name="bjw01">{{cite web |url=http://www.puroresufan.com/other/bjw/results01.php |title=2001 BJW results |accessdate=2007-05-07 |publisher=Strong Style Spirit |quote=CZW Heavyweight Title: Justice Pain (c) beat Nick Gage (12:15) with the Pain Driver. }}</ref></onlyinclude> However, ''[[Pro Wrestling Illustrated]]'' has yet to recognize it as an official world championship. Despite the "heavyweight" distinction, there is no true weight limit, as demonstrated by typically lightweight wrestlers [[Super Dragon]]<ref name="cod7" /> and [[Claude Marrow|Ruckus]].<ref name="7years" /> There have been a total of 12 recognized champions who have had a combined 29 official reigns.

